channel.title: Studio: Objects and Math :: Introduction to Web Dev
channel.description: In the exercises, you created objects to store data about the candidates for our animal astronaut corps. For this studio, we provide you with a ready-made set of candidates. You must create code to: Select the crew. Perform critical mission calculations. Determine the fuel required for launch. Select the Crew To access the code for the first part, open ObjectsStudio01.js in javascript-projects/objects-and-math/studio. Randomly Select ID Numbers Each candidate was assigned an ID number, which is stored in the candidateâ€™s data file and in the idNumbers array.
